text: Raise your hands if you give a shit about anything Steve Bannon says or believes? I thought so... very few hands. PS Why does @CNBC provide Bannon a forum whatsoever? Why should Bannon have a platform on such a legitimate stage? I don't get it but maybe others do.... @jimcramer

@jimcramer @carlquintanilla @andrewrsorkin @beckyquick Sir Larry Kudlow: How can we get "tickle down" when most of the benefits of the lower tax rates are used to buyback stock? Stated simply!

@jimcramer @SquawkCNBC @beckyquick @andrewrsorkin "Trickling Up" and Not "Trickling Down" I have, for some time, questioned whether the tax reform package would "trickle down" - arguing that it would more likely "trickle up" to those with large balance sheets (of stocks and

real estate and other assets). I believe that the absence of an improvement in real wages since yearend is testimony to the reality of my logic and view. I, for one, would like to hear the commentators at CNBC's "Delivering Alpha" to ask my buddy/pal/friend Sir Larry Kudlow
today why he and the Administration still believes that the reduction in the statutory corporate tax rate will "trickle down" to the average Joe.
